Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Systems Engineer* role with *Airship*. I bring over three years of professional experience building internal automation systems, cloud infrastructure, and production API integrations, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade infrastructure and automation systems that directly reflect the systems reliability, scripting depth, and cross-functional collaboration this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I built a Python-based MCP server using FastMCP that exposes 160+ backend actions as secure API integrations — automating enterprise SaaS workflows across multiple tenants with built-in access control and operational monitoring, precisely the kind of automation and SaaS connectivity central to this role. I engineered GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines instrumented with OpenTelemetry trace-based monitoring that tracks system health, flags regressions, and gates every release before it reaches production — giving me hands-on experience with the infrastructure automation and release quality practices Airship's Internal Systems team operates at scale. I also architected a multi-agent orchestration platform using LangGraph, LangChain, and FastAPI that routes requests across 40+ specialized sub-agents with JWT-enforced SSO-compatible authentication and identity and access control for 10,000+ users, reflecting the identity management and SSO configuration responsibilities outlined in this role. Additionally, I built live execution monitoring for long-running Temporal workflows via Redis — enabling real-time system health visibility and rapid incident response from a centralized dashboard, and automated daily PR triage across 25–30 PRs/week by scripting an agentic pipeline in Python, eliminating hours of manual operational toil. Together, these efforts reflect my ability to design scalable, observable internal systems and build the automation and API integration tooling that keeps engineering organizations efficient and reliable.

Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic infrastructure service in Java and Spring Boot — backed by PostgreSQL and Redis — that handled file operations seamlessly across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs across both on-premises and cloud environments, directly mirroring the hybrid infrastructure ownership this role requires. I also orchestrated long-running jobs with AWS Step Functions and Lambda, implementing automated disaster recovery with retry and fallback logic that ensured business continuity across 100K+ weekly executions — work that demanded rigorous documentation of recovery procedures and failure modes, the same discipline Airship expects for validating and documenting disaster recovery strategies. I further optimized PostgreSQL query performance with window functions, materialized views, and targeted indexes, surfacing the results through interactive React dashboards for cross-functional stakeholders — demonstrating the collaborative, data-driven approach I bring to supporting the teams I work alongside.

I have always been passionate about delivering exceptional cross-channel customer experiences and building the reliable internal infrastructure that makes such experiences possible at scale, and I envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Airship's mission of helping world-leading brands drive customer loyalty through consistent, meaningful interactions across every channel. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

